    <section>
         <h2>Social Media Optimization</h2>
        <p>According to Dictionary.com, the definition of Social Media Optimization is “a strategy that enhances the online visibility of a company, product, or brand in interactive social media communities, as through original posts by the company or its representatives and the sharing of content by other participants in the community.” Social Media Optimization or SMO for short helps you make and boost you social media plan by constructing a relationship to target your audience in order for you to receive better results with your website.</p>
        <p>Social Media Optimization is very important in today’s culture of business. With the help of various social media platforms, businesses are able to reach areas around the world that they have not been able to reach prior to the boom of social media. It helps build a stronger online presence, increases your reach, drive more relevant traffic, generate better leads, along with many others. The few conveniences that can occur when using social media optimization is that you are able to get the news and information about your business out there quickly and more efficiently. However, there are some setbacks that can happen with all the greatness of social media optimization such as potential for embarrassment, negative feedback, time intensive, false information along with many others.</p>
        <p>In the end, I believe that Social Media Optimization is a very helpful tool for business for today day in age. We are able to broaden our networks and come up with various ideas to keep the audience all around the world informed of our brand, business, or products. On the other hand, businesses need to be careful on how they are using this platform and audiences need to be aware that everything that is on social media is not entirely truthful or genuine.</p>
